From: Keith Packard <keithp@keithp.com>
Date: Wed, 11 Feb 2026 23:04:55 -0800
Subject: machine/arm: Mark NVIC interrupt vector as read-only

If we use .data.init.enter, then the toolchain marks this section as
writable even though the vector is declared const. Switch to
.text.data.enter so the toolchain will stop doing that and avoid
linker warnings when the interrupt vector is mixed in with the
executable section.

Signed-off-by: Keith Packard <keithp@keithp.com>
---
 libc/machine/arm/interrupt.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/libc/machine/arm/interrupt.c b/libc/machine/arm/interrupt.c
index 3326bda..808a4b3 100644
--- a/libc/machine/arm/interrupt.c
+++ b/libc/machine/arm/interrupt.c
@@ -76,7 +76,7 @@ extern uint8_t __stack[];
 
 #define i(addr, name) [(addr) / 4] = (void (*)(void))arm_##name##_isr
 
-__section(".data.init.enter") void (* const __weak_interrupt_vector[])(void)
+__section(".text.init.enter") void (* const __weak_interrupt_vector[])(void)
     __attribute((aligned(128)))
     = {
           [0] = (void (*)(void))__stack,
